        <h2>How to Display Comments at the End of Topics</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Open a Standard or HTML5 Tripane skin.</li>
            <li>Select the <span class="Emphasis">Community</span> tab.</li>
            <li>Click            <span class="Emphasis">Display topic comments at the end of each topic</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Save-File.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Shared/All/General/Whats-Next.flsnp" />
        <p>Make sure you associate the skin with the target. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Skins/Process/Associating-Skins-Targets1.htm">Associating Skins with Targets</MadCap:xref>.</p>
        <p>After you generate and publish the output, you can open Feedback Explorer to view submitted comments and see how readers are using the output. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Feedback/Opening-Feedback-Explorer.htm">Opening Feedback Explorer</MadCap:xref>.</p>
